# Group Presentation Script

Our group focused on Jia Hui, a startup founder who manages a small technology team. During the empathy stage, we found that she faces strong financial pressure, heavy responsibilities, and difficulty balancing company survival with employee well-being.

In the define stage, we grouped the interview findings into four areas: company problems, team problems, leadership and communication problems, and job change problems. After discussion, we selected the job change problem as the main issue. However, we changed it to employee retention risk because the interview did not show that employees had already decided to leave.

This problem is important because it directly affects Jia Hui. If an employee leaves, she may need to spend more money on recruitment, take on more work herself, and face further project delays. Through Why and How Laddering, we found that burnout, low morale, limited benefits, and heavy workloads may increase this risk.

Our final point of view statement is: Jia Hui needs a better way to understand and manage employee concerns because losing team members would increase her financial, emotional, and leadership pressure.

This statement is focused on Jia Hui and also leaves room for different possible solutions.

